minder
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A policeman (usually senior sergeant) who directs an undercover operation, though not undercover himself; rather like a spy's `control'. Every undercover policemen has a `minder' - with whom he is in contact every day.
